result.formatted_address: 112 Pak Sha Wan, Sai Kung, Hong Kong
result.name: Padstow Restaurant & Bar

reviews.text: Had to wait over an hire for our food but we did just walk in on a busy night so fair enough. Food was excellent.  Well seasoned very good.  Steaks were under cooked by a lot but just too good quality to send back.  A bit of extra juice is no reason to complain. Unfortunately the cocktails were hideous. Bloody Marie was tomato soup and Worcestershire sauce.  Very good selection of whiskey with even monkey shoulder available. The girls serving were delightful with big smiles and the kitchen crew fun to talk too. Would go back but would definitely  help with the cocktails.
A very decent restaurant. Good food nice environment friendly staff.
Great food, nice ambiance and awesome view. Their seafood, pasta and desserts were all great. But their salad portion were a bit small.
Recommend this cosy two-storey gastro-pub. It’s worth reserving on the weekend. Fish and Chips really excellent, and staff friendly and helpful.
Very good and charming restaurant serving traditional brutish dishes. I highly recommend!
